    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-09-18</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-12-07T15:33:23Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Fair Home Health Care Act of 2007 - Amends the Fair Labor Standards Act of 1938 to exempt certain home health care workers who are employed on a casual basis from the minimum wage and maximum hour requirements under such Act. Defines employment on a &quot;casual basis&quot; as employment which is irregular or intermittent and does not exceed 20 hours per week in the aggregate.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
